title.narrative: Improving Availability of ReproduCtive HEalth Services in the ARMM

description.narrative: The ARCHES project intends to contribute to poverty reduction and improved well -being of population in the Philippines through better and more equitable access to health services. Specifically, it will improve the availability of and access to basic Sexual and Reproductive Health (SRH) services for underserved women and young people in the Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao (ARMM). By December 2019, the project aims to achieve the following: 1) Enhanced delivery of SRH services through strengthened local monitoring networks and developed capacities of SRH service providers at the Local Government Unit level; 2) Strengthened capacity of women and young people, and their communities to develop, manage and sustain their own SRH actions in collaboration with support networks; 3) Reproductive health needs and rights effectively addressed in local and development policies, strategies and plans. The first result will enhance the supply side of the sexual and reproductive health system through the conduct of specialized training and learning and sharing sessions for health professionals, development of knowledge products and provision of equipment and improvement of facilities. The second result will focus on the increasing the demand side of sexual and reproductive health system by changing the health seeking behavior of the women and young people and their communities. This will be achieved by organizing the target communities and providing them with information that are culturally sensitive. Small groups shall also be formed to mobilize changes by having community plans and eventually these groups will demand for a better, accessible sexual and reproductive health services. The last result is advocacy work that will influence public and private institutions from the national down to the local governments.
